text:
Not sure which comment was removed. Sometimes comments get deleted even before i get to see it. No idea why it happens.

Coming to your feedback, the fact is that the hardest part of anyone's career is finding their very first job. This is 100% true.
And it's more difficult now due to the amount of graduates passing every year. There are more candidates than the no of job openings for freshers.

Having said that, there are thousands of freshers who still find the job they need. Its just that you need to prepare a lot harder and keep trying for a very long time.

I am sorry, if you have had difficulty in finding the right job and I want to say you are not alone but I also want to say, do not loose hope. 

Your efforts will never go in vain. 
By doing all the steps I mentioned in this video, will just give you the best shot at finding your first DA job. This can make your profile stand out from the rest of the crowd. But there will other candidates who may do also have such similar profiles.
So building some really good projects can really help.
Keep trying and you will achieve your goals. Never loose hope.
